A skier died today after crashing during a televised World Cup skicross event.

Canadian racer Nick Zoricic died from head injuries after smashing directly into safety nets lining the side of the course.

Television images showed Mr Zoricic tumbling through the nets as his skis and poles were thrown clear in Grindelwald, Switzerland, after he went wide on the final jump.

