Crash: Mr Zoricic was a hugely talented skier

Mr Zoricic has raced on the World Cup circuit for more than three years and was competing in his 36th event.

He was eighth in the 2011 World Championships at Deer Valley, Utah.

He is the second Canadian skier to die this season.

In January, 29-year-old freestyle skier Sarah Burke died following a training accident on a halfpipe in Utah.

Mr Zoricic was a member of the Craigleith Ski Club in Ontario.

